config.markdown:
###### HeartKit: ECG AI Heart Analysis

__HeartKit__ is an AI Development Kit (ADK) that enables developers to easily train and deploy real-time heart-monitoring models onto Ambiq's family of ultra-low power SoCs. The kit provides a variety of datasets, efficient model architectures, heart-related tasks, and model zoo. 

In this demo, we showcase two models: __ECG denoising__ and __ECG segmentation__.

__ECG denoising__ is the process of removing noise caused by several sources such as baseline wander, muscle artifacts, electrode contact movement. We leverage an AI denoiser to efficiently and effectively remove high levels of noise seen in wearable environments. 

__ECG Segmentation__ is the process of delineating key segments of the ECG signal, including the P-wave, QRS complex, and T-wave. These segments are used to compute a number of clinically relevant metrics, including heart rate, heart rate variability, QRS duration, and QT interval. They are also useful for a variety of downstream tasks such as heartbeat classification and arrhythmia detection.
